title: In Freedom's Cause
creator: G. A. Henty
description: LibriVox recording of In Freedom's Cause by G.A. Henty Another stirring tale from the master of historical fiction set in the time of Robert Bruce and William Wallace and their struggle for Scotland's independence. (Summary by Annise) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B Part 1 (159MB) Download M4B Part 2 (121MB)
subject: Librivox;audiobook;English;Historical Fiction;Scotland
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: This is a great book. It can be slow at times, but I still enjoyed it. The first couple of readers were very easy to understand, but the last one it was very hard to understand, so I had to read it myself.
reviews.reviewtitle: Good book, some good readers, another - not so good.

reviews.reviewbody: As a younger boy I enjoyed reading many G.A. Henty books. I really enjoyed listening to this audiobook while working on other things, as I don't have time to read books myself anymore.
